LoadingScreen/Help66,Sunken Guardians temporary immobilze enemies when they strike them. They also benefit from Dragon Melee Attacks.=4166
LoadingScreen/Help67,Phlogiston Guardians are detectors. They also benefit from Dragon Fire Attacks.=4167
LoadingScreen/Help68,Dragon buildings benefit from Dragon Plate Armor. Their durability can be further increased with Dragon Lineage.=4168
LoadingScreen/Help69,Dragon Fire Attacks increase the damage of all Dragon units and structures that attack with flame projectiles.=4169
LoadingScreen/Help70,Dragon Melee Attacks increase the damage of all Dragon units and structures that attack with a physical extension of themselves.=4170
LoadingScreen/Help71,Dragon Scale Armor increases the armor of all Light Dragon units.=4171
LoadingScreen/Help72,Dragon Plate Armor increases the armor of all Armored Dragon units and structures.=4172
LoadingScreen/Help73,Killing a primary Dragon structure destroys all of its propogated secondary structures.=4173
LoadingScreen/Help74,Denizens of the Deep can convert between minerals and vespene gas when Abundance is upgraded.=4174
LoadingScreen/Help75,Razorbacks have upgrades that can cause them to damage attackers, increase the amount of supply they provide, and make them more durable.=4175
LoadingScreen/Help76,Fervid Reconstitution makes Flamespitters move faster when attacking instead of slower, as well as increasing their damage by 1. It is a must have to bring your Flamespitters on the offensive.=4176
LoadingScreen/Help77,Feast increases maximum Hunter life and provides them with life gain on hit. It can elevate Hunters from harassment units to your core army.=4177
LoadingScreen/Help78,The Horned Magus's Fire Shield can be used offensively or defensively. It increases the targets armor but it also deals great damage to all nearby units that aren't also fireshielded, enemy and ally alike.=4178
LoadingScreen/Help79,The Horned Magus's Shroud can be used to get the jump on your enemies or to make a hasty get away.=4179
LoadingScreen/Help80,The Horned Magus's Invigorate is one of the only way Dragon units can heal.=4180
LoadingScreen/Help81,To build Unseen Beasts you must first research them in the Lesser Deep One's Augmentation Pit.=4181
LoadingScreen/Help82,Unseen Beasts make excellent scouts in addition to crushing enemy worker lines with their Keep Senses ability and their high survivability.=4182
LoadingScreen/Help83,Madness forces nearby enemies to attack Berserkers, preventing them from attacking your less durable units or escaping. It also makes them highly effective against Banelings.=4183
LoadingScreen/Help84,Ember Core increases a Skyrazer's range by its current cliff level. This can increase its range by up to 3, making it an excellent defense against flying siege units.=4184
LoadingScreen/Help85,The Hand of Power's Crushing Gravity also affects units that enter its area after it has been casted. It is extra effective against air units because it prevents them from attacking and forces them to the ground.=4185
LoadingScreen/Help86,The Hand of Power's Frenzy affects all biological units. It can be used not only to increase the damage output of your units, but also to soften and clean up fleeing biological enemies.=4186
LoadingScreen/Help87,Infernal Breath increases the range of Brimstone Demolishers, vastly increasing the amount of enemies they can roast.=4187
LoadingScreen/Help88,Proliferation reduces the build time of Fleshrenders. This can be used to quickly build a large amount of map control, or to counter heavily specialized armies.=4188
LoadingScreen/Help89,Celerity increases the rate at which Aurora Conduits attack, causing them not only to deal more damage but also further reduce enemy armor.=4189
LoadingScreen/Help90,Plasma Catalyst increases the rate at which Volcanic Harbingers can produce Overload charges, allowing them to obliterate enemies more quickly than before.=4190
LoadingScreen/Help91,Volcanic Harbingers deal splash damage to your own units with Overload. However, they never deal splash damage to Shades.=4191
LoadingScreen/Help92,Wraith Night prevents Shades from decaying when near a friendly Grim Glider. This can cause a powerful push to be game ending.=4192
LoadingScreen/Help93,Shades can't be controlled and deal half the damage and have half the life of their parent unit. This means that as your enemy accumulate upgrades, your Shades produced by their units are effectively weaker.=4193
LoadingScreen/Help94,Dragon units with Fire attacks have Retarget, which prevents them from wasting shots.=4194
LoadingScreen/Help95,Many Dragon units have different weapons for melee and ranged attacks which benefit from separate upgrades. Flamespitters for example deal reduced damage in melee.=4195
LoadingScreen/Help96,Frontier Deep Ones have a more powerful version of Invigorate that can simultaneously heal large numbers of biological units.=4196
LoadingScreen/Help97,Propogate Genesis Pits from your Deep Ones to increase your army production rate.=4197
LoadingScreen/Help98,Propogate Augmentation Pits from your Deep Ones to access upgrades and higher tier units.=4198
LoadingScreen/Help99,Dragon Lineage provides all Dragon units and structures with life regeneration outside of combat, as well as increasing the durability of Dragon structures.=4199

Param/Value/lib_03673618_1EEB4501,Hello! Thanks for playing my mod!<n/><n/>This is the first mod i've released, most of my modding experience came from playing around in the galaxy editor for fun. I go by Mircea Hinestraza online. I am a guy who loves to play around with cool ideas but kinda struggles putting them into paper so its impressive i actually got anything published this time.<n/>If you havent noticed yet, this mod's creation is directly inspired by <c val="80FFFF">Scion Custom Races</c> by <c val="FFFF80">Solstice</c>, and other custom race mods that have been keeping this game fresh throughout all this time.<n/><n/>This mod is still largely unfinished and i will do my best to keep it updated and in functioning quality, the mod itself is a dirty mess behind the screens so its likely i will re-make it from scratch once i have a stable vision for the project, for hygene's sake and for compatibility with other mods and custom maps. <n/><n/>I am not very good creating audiovisual assets so most of them will be ripped and modified assets by other creators, so far without their explicit consent, though most of them are ok with it or inactive, but nevertheless here's a link to the pastebin in case you havent seen it in the mod description. Param/Value/lib_03673618_9DEB3612,Some things you should know...=9181
Param/Value/lib_03673618_ABCE777C,In case you know nothing about this mod, here's the basics, i'll leave the rest for you to figure out yourself though.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Basic Gameplay</c>:<n/><n/>- The Myco-Synaptic Choir, or MycoChoir for short, is your town hall, from it you can build every building the race has to offer at any time, anywhere on the map within a <c val="FF8000">Requisition Field</c>, much like in command and conquer, however, unlike in C&C the buildings with be built without interrupting the MycoChoir's function, so with a single one you can build any amount of structures simultaneously.  [Subject to change if necessary].<n/><n/>- The buildings on the second row are your productions structures, the <c val="FFFF80">Garrison</c>, the <c val="FFFF80">Assembly </c>and the <c val="FFFF80">Hangar</c>. Assigned to infantry, Mech and Air respectively, below them you have their specific tech structures you need to build next to progress further down the tech tree.<n/><n/>- The <c val="FF8000">Requisition Field</c> is the orange circle that surrounds the Myco-Processors and the (green circles around) Myco-Choirs and Greater Processors; its analogous to the protoss pylon energy field, however, it doesn't work in exactly the same manner. Some units and structures require the abilities to be cast within a requisition field, and all buildings, including some units, require a requisition field source nearby in order to function.<n/><n/>- All production buildings can be upgraded to a "super" variant that unlocks more advanced units and produces 25% faster, however, they require a <c val="80FF00">super requisition source (the green ones) </c>around them in order to function, in other words, a Myco-Choir and a Greater Processor nearby. You can upgrade Myco-Processors within super requisition sources into Greater Processors to expand the area. <n/><n/>- Prospectors [Name subject to change] are your main worker unit, they are used to build MycoChoirs, but can also transform into a number of defensive buildings that the MycoChoir is unable to deploy (for balance's sake).<n/><n/>- Servitors are your basic unit, they start off unable to attack air and only have slightly less health and DPS than a marine, however, they are smaller, cheaper, and can pack more of them in a smaller area, increasing their volume of fire. You can upgrade their health and equip them with missile launchers in the Bio-Synth Facility<n/><n/>- Cremators are an army defense unit, they have decent range and DPS and do damage in a line. While not nearly as mobile as hellions they can be upgraded to have a shield capable of intercepting missiles<n/><n/>- The Censer is your basic means of Bio healing, once their signature ability is enabled, they will become stationary and heal units in a decent radius, instead of bleeding energy, each heal will deplete energy, so be not afraid of using them.<n/><n/>- The warden airship is your basic means of transport, it can hold 2 extra units than the every other transport and it is capable of shielding and locking down enemy units at the cost of draining its own energy. - Hailstorm Turrets are your basic means of base defense, they can air and ground units, however they have separate weapons that work differently. The hellstorm missile pods are its basic readily available ground attack, which fires slow moving AOE projectiles that can be dodged by a unit that moves fast enough [Subject to change], <c val="FFFF80">The hailstorm dont start out with the anti-air weapon enabled, you have to enable it by researching it in the Satelite Uplink</c> [Subject to change]<n/><n/>- The Sat-Com Tower is a caster building useful for base defense, can reveal enemy units, repair mechanical units and summon small drones to help defend the base in case of emergencies. <n/><n/>- The Karolean Walker is your giant mech unit, slow but powerful long range attacks. Buffs friendly units by giving them +1 armor and +2 range directly under them, use them along the rest of your army for stronger pushes. Reveals iself while attacking.=9182

I go by Mircea Hinestraza online. I am a guy who loves to play around with cool ideas but kinda struggles putting them into paper so its impressive i actually got anything published this time.<n/>If you havent noticed yet, this mod's creation is directly inspired by <c val="80FFFF">Scion Custom Races</c> by <c val="FFFF80">Solstice</c>, and other custom race mods that have been keeping this game fresh throughout all this time.<n/><n/>This mod is still largely unfinished and i will do my best to keep it updated and in functioning quality, the mod itself is a dirty mess behind the screens so its likely i will re-make it from scratch once i have a stable vision for the project, for hygene's sake and for compatibility with other mods and custom maps. <n/><n/>I am not very good creating audiovisual assets so most of them will be ripped and modified assets by other creators, so far without their explicit consent, though most of them are ok with it or inactive, but nevertheless here's a link to the pastebin in case you havent seen it in the mod description. Param/Value/lib_03673618_DCCE6512,Some things you should know...=9186
Param/Value/lib_03673618_FECBEBF3,In case you know nothing about this mod, here's the basics, i'll leave the rest for you to figure out yourself though.<n/><n/><c val="FFFF80">Basic Gameplay</c>:<n/><n/>- The Myco-Synaptic Choir, or MycoChoir for short, is your town hall, from it you can build every building the race has to offer at any time, anywhere on the map within a <c val="FF8000">Requisition Field</c>, much like in command and conquer, however, unlike in C&C the buildings with be built without interrupting the MycoChoir's function, so with a single one you can build any ammount of structures simultaneously.  [Subject to change if necessary].<n/><n/>- The buildings on the second row are your productions structures, the <c val="FFFF80">Garrison</c>, the <c val="FFFF80">Assembly </c>and the <c val="FFFF80">Hangar</c>. Assigned to infantry, Mech and Air respectively, below them you have their specific tech structures you need to build next to progress further down the tech tree.<n/><n/>- The <c val="FF8000">Requisition Field</c> is the orange circle that surrounds the Myco-Processors and the (green circles around) Myco-Choirs and Greater Processors; its analogous to the protoss pylon energy field, however, it doesnt work in exactly the same manner. Some units and structures require the abilities to be cast within a requisition field, and all buildings, including some units, require a requisition field source nearby in order to function.<n/><n/>- All production buildings can be upgraded to a "super" variant that unlocks more advanced units and produces 25% faster, however, they require a <c val="80FF00">super requisition source (the green ones) </c>around them in order to function, in other words, a Myco-Choir and a Greater Processor nearby. You can upgrade Myco-Processors within super requisition sources into Greater Processors to expand the area. <n/><n/>- Prospectors [Name subject to change] are your main worker unit, they are used to build MycoChoirs, but can also transform into a number of defensive buildings that the MycoChoir is unable to deploy (for balance's sake).<n/><n/>- Servitors are your basic unit, they start off unable to attack air and only have slightly less health and DPS than a marine, however, they are smaller, cheaper, and can pack more of them in a smaller area, increasing their volume of fire. You can upgarde their health and equip them with missile launchers in the Bio-Synth Facility<n/><n/>- Cremators are the only unit exclusive to the Super Garrison, they have decent range and DPS and do damage in a line. While not nearly as mobile as hellions they can be upgraded to have a shield capable of intercepting missiles<n/><n/>- The Censer is your basic means of Bio healing, once their signature ability is enabled, they will become stationary and heal units in a decent radius, instead of bleeding energy, each heal will deplete energy, so be not afraid of using them.<n/><n/><n/>- The warden airship is your basic means of transport, it can hold 2 extra units than the every other transport and it is capable of shielding and locking down enemy units at the cost of draining its own energy. - Hailstorm Turrets are your basic means of base defense, they can air and ground units, however they have separate weapons that work differently. The hellstorm missile pods are its basic readily available ground attack, which fires slow moving AOE projectiles that can be dodged by a unit that moves fast enough [Subject to change], <c val="FFFF80">The hailstorm dont start out with the anti-air weapon enabled, you have to enable it by researching it in the Satelite Uplink</c> [Subject to change]<n/><n/>- The Sat-Com Tower is a caster building useful for base defense, can reveal enemy units, repair mechanical units and summon small drones to help defend the base in case of emergencies. <n/><n/>- The Karolean Walker is your giant mech unit, slow but powerful long range attacks. Buffs friendly units by giving them +1 armor and +2 range directly under them, use them along the rest of your army for stronger pushes.=9187

UserData/PatchInfoNewFeatures/1_Patch Notes,Have been fought from RTS to MMO-RPG, and even in a mystical Team Brawler game. Today, he has returned to play RTS games.<n/><n/>Now introduce the 1st Melee AI, in the history of the whloe Mod: <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Terr">Thrall - the Warchief of the Horde</s>.<n/><n/>You can team up with him or fight him as a enemy. For new players of the RTS series, the former option is advised, because of reasons.<n/><n/>As a <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Terr">AI Commander</s>, Thrall plays Orc (of course), and his starting hero is always <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Prot">Far Seer</s> - HIMSELF (it's just a Far Seer skin, all his balance data is the same as the melee Far Seer).<n/><n/>Thrall's secondary hero would be randomly chosen between the <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Prot">Tauren Chieftain</s> and the <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Prot">Shadow Hunter</s> (Why no Blademaster, you ask? Come on, what's the point of using the Blademaster as the 2nd hero in Melee?)<n/><n/>While you are teaming up with Thrall, don't forget to use <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Terr">AI communication</s> <k val="AICommunication" count="1"/> button  to give him instructions - the Warchief is so kindly that instead of executing you in the name of the Horde, he would occasionally listen to you (totally unexpectedly, I know. hail to the Warchief)!<n/><n/><n/><s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Prot">Ending Spoiler:</s> After the Thrall AI goes stable, the next big thing of the mod would be a new map - <s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Zerg">(4)TurtleRock</s>, which features a Tavern.=28582

UserData/PatchInfoNewFeatures/3_Title,Tome Of Retraing=28587
UserData/PatchInfoNotes/1_Patch Notes,<s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Zerg">Mod Changes</s><n/><ul indent="2" text="•"><li>Thrall AI Online!</li><li>Now you can build on Ramp!</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Ghoul </s>and <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Goblin Shredder</s> no longer be count as Army (F4) while they are <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Gathering</s>, and won't be selected by Army Select(F4) button. While non-harvesting ones would be count in the army number, and can be select by F4.</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Mechanical Critter</s> no longer count as Army (F4)</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Blademaster</s>'s <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Bladestorm</s>(Both HD and Non-HD) now get a new visual art.(the official one is broken)</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Spirit Walker</s>'s <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Ethereal </s>form get a new visual art.</li><li>Mind controlled Creeps would no longer try to go back to their original camp.</li><li>Changed <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Human Architecture </s>upgrade to be no longer use triggers, so that map makers could modify it much easier.</li><li>Changed the Higher Ground Missing System to no longer use triggers.</li><li>While attaking from within FoW(e.g. attack a ground unit from higher cliff), the attacker would be fully revealed to the victim (victim would fully gain the vision of the attacking unit), instead of just reveal a snapshot like SC2 does.</li><li>Changed the mechanism of Shock Wave, this ability no use max damage as its limitation instead of max target. (Can potentially hits more targets) </li><li>Optimized the spell:<s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg"> Control Magic</s>.</li><li>Map makers who used this mod can now change the Max damage of the Shock Wave ability via <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelText_Terr">Data Editor->User Type->Ability Data - Shock Wave</s></li><li>Map makers who used this mod can now change the Healing Amount of Healing Wave via <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelText_Terr">Data Editor->User Type->Ability Data - Healing Wave</s></li><li>Map makers who used this mod can now change the cost fact of Control Magic via <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelText_Terr">Data Editor->User Type->Ability Data - Control Magic</s></li><li>Animation of immediately start moving after staring a spell now blends more smoothly (e.g. <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Archmage </s>moves immediately after casting <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Summoner Water Element</s>)</li></ul><n/><n/><n/><s val="HelpControlsPanelHeader_Zerg">Bug Fixes</s><n/><ul indent="2" text="•"><n/><li>Fixed a potential leak with the actor: <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelText_Terr">War3_SwapableMissileAttackImpactModel</s>.</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Mass Teleport</s> and <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Scroll of Town Portal</s> would be forcely cancelled if the target dies in the progress.</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Frost Wyrm</s> no longer be considered as 'Powerful Creep'(Immunity to all abilities that can't be used on Heroes).</li><li>Fixed the attacking animation of the <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Montain King</s> under <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Avatar </s>form.(It's actually a bug in the official model's animation priory)</li><li>Fixed a issue that make <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Dragon Turtle</s>, <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Elder Hydra</s>, and <s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Prot">Firelord</s>'s splash damage could destroy items.</li><li>Flyer units no longer have chance to miss while attacking for a lower cliff.</li><li><s val="HelpGameMechanicsPanelHeader_Zerg">Earthquake </s>no longer affects on trees and items.</li><li>While your hero and enmemy hero stand in font of the same non-Netrual shop, the shop would be no longer play annoying sounds.</li></ul>=28588

WESTRING_AIFLAG_RANDOMPATHS_TIP,With this option enabled, the AI will tend to choose destinations in a more random fashion.=29627
WESTRING_AIFLAG_REMOVEINJURIES,Remove Injuries=29628
WESTRING_AIFLAG_REMOVEINJURIES_TIP,Enable this option to periodically send injured units home (or to a Fountain of Life) to recover.=29629
WESTRING_AIFLAG_REPAIRS,Repair Structures=29630
WESTRING_AIFLAG_REPAIRS_TIP,Enable this option to have workers automatically repair structures when needed.=29631
WESTRING_AIFLAG_SETPLAYERNAME,Set Player Name=29632
WESTRING_AIFLAG_SETPLAYERNAME_TIP,Enable this option to use the AI name above as the player name.=29633
WESTRING_AIFLAG_SLOWHARVEST,Slow Harvesting=29634
WESTRING_AIFLAG_SLOWHARVEST_TIP,With this option enabled, only 1 gold or wood will be harvested by workers instead of the normal amount.  This gives the AI a significant economic handicap.=29635
WESTRING_AIFLAG_SMARTART,Smart Artillery=29636
WESTRING_AIFLAG_SMARTART_TIP,With this option enabled, artillery units will attempt to come forward and mount a siege attack on the enemy base when possible.=29637
WESTRING_AIFLAG_TAKEITEMS,Take Items=29638
WESTRING_AIFLAG_TAKEITEMS_TIP,With this option enabled, Heroes will attempt to pick up any useful items they encounter.=29639
WESTRING_AIFLAG_TARGETHEROES,Target Heroes=29640
WESTRING_AIFLAG_TARGETHEROES_TIP,With this option enabled, the AI will place a higher priority on attacking Heroes during battle.=29641
WESTRING_AIFLAG_UNITSFLEE,Units Flee=29642
WESTRING_AIFLAG_UNITSFLEE_TIP,With this option enabled, non-Hero units will attempt to flee from battle if they are seriously injured or unable to attack.=29643
WESTRING_AIFLAG_WATCHMEGA,Have No Mercy=29644
WESTRING_AIFLAG_WATCHMEGA_TIP,With this option enabled, the AI will watch for opportunities to attack when the enemy appears to be weakened or at a disadvantage.</n></n>Note that these attacks correspond to the 'Enemy - Major Assault' target type.=29645
